io.smudgr.app.view

Interface FileDialog.FileDialogCallback

  • Enclosing class:
    FileDialog

    public static interface FileDialog.FileDialogCallback
    The FileDialog.FileDialogCallback interface allows passing behavior for what to do when the file chooser is resolved, either from user cancellation or actual file selection.
    See Also:
    FileDialog.show(actionName, allowMultiselect, fileFilter, callback)

    • Method Detail

      • onSelection

        void onSelection(java.io.File[] selectedFiles)
        Callback with the user selected file(s)

        The selectedFiles array will never be empty and if multi-selection isn't allowed, there will only be on selected file.

        Parameters:
        selectedFiles - Never empty, length one if multi-select was not allowed

      • onFailure

        void onFailure(java.lang.String reason)
        Callback with reason for failure.

        This is called if the user manually cancelled for didn't select any files.

        Parameters:
        reason - Failure message.
